itemDescription: 1881-1960; Scottish archaeologist, epigraphist, classicist, and academic

wikipedia_page.main: Sir William Moir Calder, FBA (2 July 1881 – 17 August 1960) was a Scottish archaeologist, epigraphist, classicist, and academic. He was Hulme Professor of Greek at the University of Manchester from 1913 to 1930, and Professor of Greek at the University of Edinburgh from 1930 to 1951.
